The paper proposes a new Generalized Consensus protocol for geographically replicated sites, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the performance of the protocol in the presence of conflicting requests, which relates to the sub-category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The protocol is designed to improve the speed of consensus, which is a key aspect of Operating Systems (cs.OS). The paper also discusses the security of the protocol, which falls under the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). Finally, the protocol is designed to handle multiple leaders, which relates to the sub-category of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
